snippet.title: Indiana Fever Put on a SHOW in 35-Point Opening Day Win Over Chicago Sky | FULL Game Highlights
snippet.description: Caitlin Clark dropped a triple-double with 20 points, 10 assists & 10 rebounds, Aliyah Boston added a double-double with 19 points, 13 rebounds & 5 blocks and Kelsey Mitchell and Natasha Howard each scored 15 points to lead the Fever to their largest season-opening win in franchise history, 93-58, over the Sky.

it.title: Ho costruito Minecraft per un vero axolotl!
it.description:
Ho costruito un VERO Minecraft per il mio axolotl!

Dopo aver visto il nuovo film di Minecraft, sapevo di doverlo costruire nella vita reale per i miei axolotl, Miso e Matcha! In questo episodio, cuciniamo persino un vero pollo di Minecraft per la mia adorabile gattina ragdoll, Nori! Guardate fino alla fine per vedere i miei axolotl Miso e Matcha reagire al vero Minecraft! Questa costruzione ha richiesto molto tempo e impegno, ma penso che

â™¡ Acquista il merchandising: https://aquariuminfo.com/ (spedizioni in tutto il mondo ğŸŒ)

ISCRIVITI per avere la possibilitÃ  di vincere il kit ecosistema
â–º https://www.youtube.com/c/AquariumInfo?sub_confirmation=1

Incontra la squadra! ğŸˆ Nori
ğŸ² Gizmo
ğŸ¦€ Noodle e Cetrioli
ğŸ¦ Mochi
ğŸ¢ Harry
ğŸ¦ Ralph
ğŸ¸ Frito e Burrito
ğŸ¦ Lucy e Limone
ğŸ  Arachidi e Marmellata
ğŸ¦ Lime e Pepe e Squeak
ğŸª¦ R.I.P. Kirby

Guardate mentre costruiamo un epico ecosistema Minecraft IRL per oltre $ 5.000 per i miei axolotl, Miso e Matcha. I miei axolotl hanno recentemente avuto dei cuccioli - Miso e Matcha - e sono finalmente abbastanza grandi da vivere insieme! Quindi oggi stiamo costruendo per loro l'ecosistema domestico dei loro sogni. Questo terrario da $ 5.000 si estende su diversi biomi di Minecraft, tra cui una foresta gigante con piante vere, una montagna innevata, un bioma di funghi, un villaggio di Minecraft e una grotta lussureggiante! Abbiamo persino dei veri mob che vivono nel nostro ecosistema Minecraft, come la mia lucertola Ringo, il piccolo pesce rasbora e altro ancora! Riesci a individuarli tutti?

In questo episodio ricco di avventure, viaggiamo nella natura selvaggia per vivere Minecraft dal vivo, alla ricerca di veri mob di Minecraft. Costruiamo anche un vulcano fai da te stampato in 3D per sperimentare la produzione di vera lava per il nostro ecosistema Minecraft.

Guarda tutto il video per vedere i miei axolotl Miso e Matcha divertirsi con il loro nuovo ecosistema Minecraft DA SOGNO! Questo video Ã¨ perfetto per chiunque ami Minecraft, Minecraft nella vita reale, gli axolotl, gli animali esotici, gli animali rari, i progetti fai da te o sia semplicemente interessato a sapere come allevare gli axolotl come animali domestici!

Se hai commenti, suggerimenti o domande per questo video di Minecraft nella vita reale o per i video futuri, lasciali nei commenti! Per contenuti aggiuntivi come questo, tutorial video, anteprime di progetti e altro ancora, seguimi su Instagram @aquariuminfo.

Se stai leggendo questo, sei un Super Fan! Commenta "Lava Chicken" cosÃ¬ ti noto ğŸŒ‹ğŸ“

snippet.title: The Birth of BABY BLOBS (Pt. 1): Blob Universe #9
snippet.description:
The journey continues.....Let's keep going and see how many blob characters I can add to the collection today. It's going to be a lot of sculpting, customizing, and BLOBS. 

CHECK OUT THE AWFUL EVAN: https://moriahelizabethmerch.com/


___UPLOAD SCHEDULE___

Friday at 4:00pm ET

___________WELCOME TO MY CHANNEL__________

Hey! my name is Moriah (pronounced muh-rye-yuh) Elizabeth and this is my channel....obviously. I'm 30 and like doing creative activities (mostly painting on things), or really anything that gives me an excuse to use rainbows, sprinkles and my own cutesy characters in excess. I'm heavy into editing, so my video are chok-full of sound effects, filters and lil....moments, or as we like to call them "MEmes." I paint on squishies, thrift store finds, and various other items I find. I also love to draw, traditionally and digitally. I'm not the most skilled artist out here, but I like to focus on having fun with creativity and being able to laugh at my own mistakes. 

CURRENT SERIES:
Squishy Makeovers: Fixing and decorating used squishies sent from my viewers
Thrift Store Makeovers: Fixing and decorating stuff I find at thrift stores/yard sales
Bake With ME: Recreating squishies I've decorated in real life
Create This Book: Drawing in the prompt book that I wrote (available to purchase and follow along)
Squishy Unboxing: Opening used squishy packages sent from viewers
Drawings to Squishies: turning my flat drawings into squishies
Finishing Art Ideas: Choosing art ideas from my giant list and making them happen
Squishies I've Been Avoiding: Painting on the squishies I DON'T want to paint

â€œSuperman,â€ DC Studiosâ€™ first feature film to hit the big screen, is set to soar into theaters worldwide this summer from Warner Bros. Pictures.  In his signature style, James Gunn takes on the original superhero in the newly imagined DC universe with a singular blend of epic action, humor and heart, delivering a Superman whoâ€™s driven by compassion and an inherent belief in the goodness of humankind.

Fast food has never been GOOD food, but it was a quick, easy, reliable and cheap way to get a meal that appealed to people who were time poorâ€¦ or just wellâ€¦ you knowâ€¦ actually poorâ€¦
Mass layoffs, increasing economic uncertainty, deferred student loan payments kicking in and spiking levels of consumer debt SHOULD be the perfect opportunity for these cheap offerings to bring in customers who donâ€™t have much money to spare, but still want to eat. 
For a long time companies like McDonalds, Dominos, KFC, Taco Bell and Wendyâ€™s were considered â€œrecession proofâ€ because even in the most dire of circumstances people still need to eat, and the companies typically offered the best exchange rate of dollars to calories in the market. 
But thatâ€™s changed. 
In a business move that can only be described asâ€¦ confusingâ€¦ These brands have responded to cost conscious, busy and desperate consumers by becoming more expensive, slower and less reliableâ€¦ 
Unsurprisingly sales across the industry have plummeted at a time when they SHOULD be outperforming. 
It would almost be comical if they werenâ€™t collectively some of the largest employers in the country.
However the McRessession has been caused by more than some management missteps, itâ€™s a clear sign of some much bigger problems in the wider economy.

snippet.title: CarÃ­n LeÃ³n: Tiny Desk Concert
snippet.description:
Felix Contreras | May 16, 2025
CarÃ­n LeÃ³n is an old soul. There is no other way to account for the power of the emotion in his voice. His 16-piece band tests the limited space behind the Tiny Desk, but when the brass takes over to punctuate a performance, Leon's commanding presence shows why he's one of the best at what he does.

Regional Mexican music is based upon song forms from another era, but LeÃ³n's lyrics add a new spin on heartbreak and love lost. This set opens with "Ese Vato No Te Queda," followed by two songs from the 2024 album Palabra De To's. Previously, LeÃ³n premiered "Primera Cita" for his Tiny Desk (home) concert, which became a major hit. That song "left a mark on our lives and completely shaped our careers," he shares. For good luck, LeÃ³n here premieres "Por la Suave," which was also written by Alejandro Lozano. "A poem that I love," LeÃ³n says.

snippet.title: Gary Sinise Speaks Out About His Son's Death & Why He Left Hollywood | PEOPLE
snippet.description:
Gary Sinise shares his story of stepping away from Hollywood to care for his family and grieve the unimaginable loss of his son, Mac. The actor opens up for the first time about Macâ€™s battle with chordoma, a rare, slow-growing spinal cancer, and the strength his son showed throughout his illness: â€œThe way he dealt with it was just pure grace and courage.â€ He reveals the moment they discovered Macâ€™s tumor on a CT scan, after months of unexplained pain: â€œIt looks like a monster grabbing my sonâ€™s spine.â€ Gary reflects on a harrowing period that began with his fatherâ€™s stroke, followed by his wifeâ€™s stage 3 breast cancer treatment and his sonâ€™s shocking diagnosis â€” and the decision he made to pause acting to care for them. Mac passed away on January 5, 2024. Garyâ€™s wife is now cancer-free.

He has continued his work with the Gary Sinise Foundation, which supports veterans, first responders, and their families. Gary recently produced â€˜Brothers After Warâ€™, a documentary about wounded heroes returning from combat, and is helping release Macâ€™s final music. The songs are now available, with proceeds going to the Foundation in honor of Macâ€™s wishes. Gary also shares the joy he finds in being a grandfather, a role that brings light amid the pain. He will return to Washington, D.C. to host the Foundationâ€™s annual Memorial Day concert. Gary Sinise offers an intimate look at life, loss, and legacy in the wake of profound personal tragedy.

snippet.description:
The granddaddy of all barn finds! A 1966 Ford GT40 that had been stashed in a barn since 1982 now sees the light of day. In total, only 100 GT40s were madeâ€”about 30 were built specifically for the track, while the rest were made for the road. Many of the road cars were later converted into track cars, so finding an all-original road car with all its original parts is extremely rare! Follow along as Tom and the new owner, Chad, walk around and inspect this legendary time capsule.

snippet.title: Nobody 2 | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
Nobody ruins his vacation. #Nobody2 hits theaters August 15.

---
Sometimes the most dangerous place for a dad is a family vacation.

Bob Odenkirk returns as suburban husband, father and workaholic assassin Hutch
Mansell in the new chapter to Nobody, the hit 2021 bare-knuckle action-thriller that
opened at number one at the U.S. box office.

Four years after he inadvertently took on the Russian mob, Hutch remains $30 million in debt to the criminal organization and is working it off with an unending string of hits on international thugs.

Much as he likes the slam-bang action of his â€œjob,â€ Hutch and his wife Becca
(International Emmy nominee Connie Nielsen) find themselves overworked and drifting apart. So, they decide to take their kids (Gage Munroe, Paisley Cadorath) on a short getaway to Wild Billâ€™s Majestic Midway and Waterpark, the one and only place where Hutch and his brother Harry (Grammy and Emmy nominee RZA) went on a vacation as kids.

With Hutchâ€™s dad (Emmy winner Christopher Lloyd) in tow, the family arrives in the small tourist town of Plummerville (â€œPlummerville is Summerville!â€), eager for some fun in the sun.
But when a minor encounter with some town bullies yanks the family into the crosshairs of a corrupt theme-park operator (John Ortiz; Fast and Furious franchise, Bumblebee) and his shady sheriff (Emmy and Golden Globe nominee Colin Hanks), Hutch finds himself the focus of the most unhinged, blood-thirsty crime boss he (or anyone) has ever encountered (Emmy winning and OscarÂ® nominated screen icon, Sharon Stone).

Nobody 2 is an 87North/Eighty Two Films/Odenkirk Provissiero Entertainment
production, directed by Timo Tjahjanto (The Night Comes for Us, The Big 4). The
screenplay is by returning writer Derek Kolstad (John Wick, Die Hart) and by Aaron
Rabin (Tom Clancyâ€™s Jack Ryan), from a story by Derek Kolstad, based on characters created by Derek Kolstad. This filmâ€™s returning producers are 87North founders Kelly McCormick (Bullet Train, The Fall Guy) and David Leitch (Bullet Train, The Fall Guy); Odenkirk Provissiero Entertainment founder Marc Provissiero (No Hard Feelings, PEN15), Eighty Two Films founder Braden Aftergood (Hell or High Water, Samaritan); and Bob Odenkirk (Better Call Saul, Breaking Bad). The executive producer is David Hyman.

snippet.title: Jeff Teague REACTS to Pacers ENDING Cavs, Thunder take lead on Nuggets, Jayson Tatum torn achilles
snippet.description:
On the Wednesday, May 14 episode of 520 in the Morning, Jeff Teague, DJ Wells, and B Hen react to Tyrese Haliburton and the Indiana Pacers advancing to the eastern conference finals for the second year in a row after finishing off Donovan Mitchell and the Cleveland Cavaliers in 5 games. Jeff reacts to Shai Gilgeous-Alexander and the Oklahoma City Thunder taking a 3-2 lead on Nikola Jokic and the Denver Nuggets, as well as Jayson Tatumâ€™s confirmed torn achilles which will keep him out for the entirety of next season.
